title: Kim Kardashian denies she's made a second sex tape | Daily Mail Online
text: comments Kim Kardashian is denying that she has filmed a new sex tape. Rumors of an explicit video starring the reality TV fave were reported by Britain's Mirror newspaper on Tuesday. But Kim's rep told DailyMail.com: 'It's not new - it's the same old tape.' 'Same old tape': Kim Kardashian, pictured February 14 in NYC, denied she's made a new sex tape after reports in a British newspaper claimed leaked footage was circulating online The Mirror didn't name the outlet it claims has the leaked footage allegedly showing the wife of Kanye West in lingerie on a bed. The 36-year-old, of course, was catapulted to fame after a sex tape she made with then boyfriend Ray J in 2003 was leaked and distributed in 2007 by adult entertainment brand Vivid. She accepted a $5 million settlement from the company in return for dropping her lawsuit against them. Reality star Kim, 36, found fame after a sex tape she made with then-boyfriend Ray J in 2003 leaked in 2007 and was widely distributed. She's seen in a selfie she shared last March No problem with nudity: The Keeping Up With The Kardashians star isn't shy about flaunting her body and often shares racy pics and close-ups of her cleavage and butt with fans The same year she and her family started appearing on E! in the reality show Keeping Up With The Kardashians, a series that has made all of her siblings famous too. Kim constantly flaunts her body on social media, sharing racy and sometimes nude selfies and close-ups of her cleavage and derriere. She has recently shared with fans that she's had cosmetic procedures to remove stretch marks and undergone laser hair removal. On Tuesday she took to Snapchat to explain how she's wearing a full sweat suit to try and shed another seven pounds, that would bring her weight down to 115 pounds. Back online: The mother-of-two, who is married to rapper Kanye West, has started posting again after a brief self-imposed exile from social media following her Paris robbery in October Meanwhile, her younger half-sister Kendall Jenner has been gushing about how inspirational she is. She's definitely one of the smartest and most innovative people I know,' the 21-year-old said in a post on her subscription website . 'Kim's entrepreneurial skills are incredible.' Kim, who has been married three times, shares two children with current spouse Kanye West, whom she wed in 2014. Mom duties: Kim was seen Sunday in Calabasas, California, taking her kids North, three, and Saint, one, out for a sushi lunch The couple share daughter North, three, and son Saint, one. She took time off from social media and public appearances following her robbery at gunpoint in Paris in October. She's also been dealing with Kanye's 'psychotic breakdown' that led him to be hospitalized in Los Angeles in November. But Kim is now emerging back into the spotlight and renewing her social media presence as she and her family move on from the troubles of last year. Budding beauty: The Calabasas local took some cute snaps with her niece Penelope wearing the app's sweet flower crown filter. The family oriented beauty and her team have firmly denied the existence of any new tape Flower girls! The mom of two doted on her darling niece in the flowery Snapchat. Penelope is older sister Kourtney's oldest daughter Slimmer Kim: The reality diva has been hard at work with her trainer Don trying to knock off the last few pounds before reaching her goal weight of 115 lbs
